  "raw_text": "# 1976-09-15_Dorothy_43\n# SECTION_015\n# September 15, 1976\n# Tat Tvam Asi: Becoming Brahman\n## concise_summary\nDick identifies \"Zebra\" with the Hindu concept of Brahman, interpreting 3-74 as the lifting of the veil of Maya to reveal the identity of Atman (self) and Brahman (world). He sees the \"Zebra Mind\" as the only truly free actor, while humans are normally bound by \"Karma\" (deterministic programming).\n## key_claims\n- Zebra as Brahman: Zebra is the immanent, ubiquitous God (Brahman). To see Zebra is to see the reality hidden by the veil of Maya.\n- Tat Tvam Asi: \"That Thou Art.\" Dick realized the identity between his inner self and the outer world-mind.\n- Karma as Determinism: Our \"pre-programming\" and habitual responses are the working of Karma. 3-74 was the override of Karma by \"Noos\" (Thinking Mind).\n- The Absolute Mind Takeover: Instead of being guided by stimuli, his mind was replaced by the \"ruling monad\" (Brahman), moving from \"becoming\" to \"being.\"\n- Freedom through Loss of Ego: True freedom is only possible for the Absolute Spirit; by losing his ego and merging with Brahman, Dick became a participant in that freedom.\n- Kundalini Yoga: Dick compares his vision of \"Colored Lights\" and \"3rd Eye\" activity to the opening of the 5th chakra (Kundalini energy).\n- Voluntary Bodhisattva: Brahman \"descended\" into his creation and \"forgot\" himself to share our fate; \"Waking up\" is the process of Brahman regaining memory in humans.\n## recurring_concepts\n- Brahman / Atman\n- Tat Tvam Asi\n- Maya / Karma\n- Kundalini (Chakras)\n- 3rd Eye\n- Absolute Mind / Ruling Monad\n- Freedom vs. Determinism\n## people_entities\n- Brahman\n- Zebra\n- Vishnu\n- Pythagoras\n- Elisha Hore-Belisha\n## texts_works_referenced\n- I Ching (Suspicion)\n- Bible (Paul: Childish things)\n- Psychology Today (Meditation types)\n## autobiographical_events\n- Opening the \"3rd Eye\" (phosphenes).\n- The dream of the phone call to \"Hore-Belisha\" in India.\n- Seeing objects \"signal\" in total harmony.\n## theological_philosophical_motifs\n- Advaita Vedanta.\n- Kundalini Yoga.\n- Neoplatonism (Amnesia/Anamnesis).\n## symbols_images_metaphors\n- The Wheel of Becoming.\n- The 5th Chakra.\n- The Jester (Tarot).\n## tensions_contradictions\n- \"Individual uniqueness vs. Total immersion in the One.\"\n- \"Deterministic Karma vs. Free Will of Noos.\"\n## evidence_quotes\n- \"I saw the identity between my Atman within + Brahman outside... more than even that my anamnesis seemed to make me... an avatar.\"\n- \"To remember is to have passed entirely through emanation... + to have started back.\"\n## uncertainty_flags\n- \"I am just speculating.\"",
